To create a React hook for managing the filtering state of an interactive data grid, you can use the following code:

```jsx
import { useState } from 'react';

const useGridFilterState = (initialFilters) => {
  const [filters, setFilters] = useState(initialFilters);

  // Function to update filter state based on user input
  const handleFilterChange = (key, value) => {
    setFilters((prevFilters) => ({
      ...prevFilters,
      [key]: value,
    }));
  };

  // Function to apply all filters to the data
  const applyFilters = (data) => {
    return data.filter(item =>
      Object.keys(filters).every(filterKey => item[filterKey] === filters[filterKey])
    );
  };

  // Reset all filters to initial state
  const resetFilters = () => setFilters(initialFilters);

  return { filters, handleFilterChange, applyFilters, resetFilters };
};

export default useGridFilterState;
```

This hook provides three main functions: `filters` which holds the current filter state as an object, `handleFilterChange` which updates the filter state based on user input for a specific field, `applyFilters` which filters the data based on the current filter state, and `resetFilters` which resets the filter state to its initial value.
