Building a WordPress custom post type for storing transient cache API responses is an excellent way to manage and reuse data efficiently. This approach can significantly improve the performance of your site by reducing the number of requests made to external APIs.

Here’s a step-by-step guide to creating a custom post type specifically for caching API responses:

### Step 1: Set Up Your Theme or Plugin

