csvGenerator.pipe(fs.createWriteStream('output.csv'));
```

In this example, we create a file stream that writes to `output.csv`. We then pipe our `CsvGenerator` instance through this file stream. The generator will write rows of CSV data to the output file as it is processed.

By using streams for both CSV parsing and generation in Node.js, you can efficiently handle large datasets without loading them into memory. This approach is particularly useful when dealing with CSV files that are too large to fit into available RAM.
